label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg57

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma posterior-lateral to the gnathal ganglion (Sterne et al., 2021; Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the brain, it has bilateral dendritic and axonal arborization in the gnathal ganglion (Sterne et al., 2021; Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It descends on the contralateral side af the cervical connective, follows the ventral median tract of ventral cervical fasciculus and has presynapses in the ventral association center (Sterne et al., 2021; Sturner et al., 2024). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg60

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma in the gnathal ganglion, ventral to the antennal mechanosensory and motor center (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It has bilateral dendritic and axonal arborization in the gnathal ganglion (Sterne et al., 2021; Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It descends on the contralateral side of the cervical connective and has axonal arborization in the T1 leg neuropil and intermediate tectulum (Sterne et al., 2021). Its predicted neurotransmitter is GABA (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg61

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma in the ventral gnathal ganglion, ventral to the wedge (Sterne et al., 2021; Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). It is a putative embryonic-born neuron (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the brain, it has postsynapses and presynapses in the gnathal ganglion (Sterne et al., 2021; Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). This arborization is mainly ipsilateral, but close to the midline, and it descends on the ipsilateral side (Sterne et al., 2021). In the VNC, it follows the dorsal lateral tract of dorsal cervical fasciculus (Sturner et al., 2024) and has axonal arborization in the T1 leg neuropil (Sterne et al., 2021). Its predicted neurotransmitter is acetylcholine (Eckstein et al., 2024). There are approximately 2 of these cells per organism (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024; Sturner et al., 2024).

label.value: descending neuron of the gnathal ganglion DNg70

value.value: Adult descending neuron with its soma anterior-ventral to the gnathal ganglion (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the brain, it has postsynapses and presynapses in the gnathal ganglion, the prow and the contralateral flange, as well as postsynapses in the ipsilateral flange (Schlegel et al., 2024; Dorkenwald et al., 2024). In the VNC, it follows the ventral median tract of ventral cervical fasciculus (Sturner et al., 2024).
